# Expose mempool.space frontend to the public internet
# Machine: flagrant-feedback (user: install), 2026-04-30

## 1. Change port binding in docker-compose.yml

sed -i 's/127.0.0.1:8080:8080/0.0.0.0:8080:8080/' ~/mempool-space/docker-compose.yml

# Verify:
grep 'ports' -A2 ~/mempool-space/docker-compose.yml
# Expected:
#   ports:
#     - "0.0.0.0:8080:8080"

## 2. Open firewall

sudo ufw allow 8080/tcp

# Note: UFW was inactive on this host, so no traffic was being blocked.
# Rule added for when UFW is enabled in future.

## 3. Recreate web container to pick up new port binding

sg docker -c "docker compose -f ~/mempool-space/docker-compose.yml up -d --force-recreate web"

# Verify:
sg docker -c "docker ps --format 'table {{.Names}}\t{{.Status}}\t{{.Ports}}'"
# Expected: mempool-space-web-1   Up ...   0.0.0.0:8080->8080/tcp

## Result: http://86.104.228.47:8080 is now publicly accessible.
